SINGAPORE DAYBOOK: DBS, Overseas Union, Singapore Airlines

-- B y   L i n u s   C h u a   a n d   P h o e b e   S e d g m a n
-- 
2011-04-17T22:11:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/singapore-daybook-dbs-overseas-union-singapore-airlines.html
Singapore Airlines Ltd., the
world’s second-biggest carrier by market value, said it plans to
raise fuel surcharge by between $4 and $32.  The carrier also said it filled 73.2 percent of seats in
March from 80.8 percent a year earlier. The overall  load factor 
climbed to 67.3 percent from 72.9 percent a year earlier.  WHAT TO WATCH:  *DBS Group Holdings Ltd. said it earned 250 million yuan ($38
million) of profit last year. The bank is set to have 50 Chinese
outlets by 2013.
*Guocoland Ltd. said third-quarter net income fell 79 percent to
S$2 million from a year earlier.
*LHT Holdings Ltd. said it will invest up to 20 million yuan to
establish a manufacturing facility in  China .
*Longcheer Holdings Ltd. said it expects to report a loss for
the third quarter.
*Osim International Ltd. said it plans to buy a 35 percent stake
in TWG Tea Co. for S$31.4 million.
*Overseas Union Enterprise Ltd. said it will buy the Crowne
Plaza Changi Airport Hotel for S$250 million. OUE will also buy
an adjacent block of land for S$43 million and build a 200-room
Holiday Inn Express.  ECONOMY:  *1 p.m.: March non-oil domestic exports; est. 4.5% y/y  MARKETS:  S&P 500  up 0.4% to 1,319.68
Stoxx Europe 600 up 0.3% to 277.78
MSCI Asia Pacific down 0.5% to 135.82
Straits Times Index down 0.2% to 3,153.30  BTV:  *7:10 a.m.: RBS Asia Research Manager James McCafferty
*7:40 a.m.: JPMorgan Chief Asian/EM Strategist Adrian Mowat
*8:10 a.m.: JLL Head of China Research Michael Klibaner
*9:10 a.m.: UBS WM Chief Investment Strategist Kelvin Tay
